//////////
Step to generate package.json
///////////

**NodeJs must be install in system
https://nodejs.org/en/

> go inside the folder using terminal/cmd
> type npm init
> answer all questions
> type "yes"

//////////
Step to install packages
///////////
> go inside the folder using terminal/cmd
> npm i packagename


C > Create (POST)
R > Read   (GET)
U > Update (PUT)
D > Delete (DELETE)


///////
Global package
///////

> Need admin access to install
> install in particular system
> will not add in package.json
> only packages that help to start/ build the apps

///////////
Step to install global package
///////////
#window
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g nodemon

#mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g nodemon


//////
Local
> https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
> install
> in c drive make one folder by the name of data
> inside data folder make folder db 
> c/data/db

//////Step to start mongodb server//////
> open cmd 
> go inside folder c/programm/mongodb/4.4/script/bin  (go to bin folder)
> mongod (start mongodb server on port 27017)

//////Step to start mongodb console//////
> open cmd 
> go inside folder c/programm/mongodb/4.4/script/bin  (go to bin folder)
> mongo 


Cloud
> https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
> start free
> click on "create new cluster"
> select m0 sandbox
> click "create cluster"
> on left side (select network access)
> Add IP Address
    > Access List Entry: 0.0.0.0/0
    > Comment: anything
> on left side (select database access)
> Add new database user
    > provide username and password
        (don't use any special character like $@)
    > Database User Privileges
        > Atlas Admin

