_id > object id (it is the unique value) (primary key)

12byte 
> 4 byte (timestamp)
> 5 byte (random value)
> 3 byte (counter)

//////////
Routes Required
////////
> List of city  > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/location
> List of Restaurant > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/restaurent
> Restaurant wrt to city > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/restaurent?city=1
> Quick Search > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/mealtype
> list of hotel wrt to quick Search > >https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/restaurent?mealtype=1
> Cuisine Filter > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/restaurent?cuisine=1
> Cost Filter > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/restaurent?lcost=300&hcost=400
> Sorting > http://localhost:9800/restaurent?sort=-1
> Restaurant details > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/rest/3
> Place Order > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/placeOrder
> See all Bookings > https://restapilive.herokuapp.com/orders



////find with condition/////
db.first.find({city:'London'})
db.first.find({_id:4})
db.first.find({_id:4,city:'London'})

db.restaurent.find().pretty()

> select * from restaurent where city = "1"
db.restaurent.find({city:"1"}).pretty()

                    condition,projection
db.restaurent.find({city:"1"},{city:1,cost:1,name:1}).pretty()


db.restaurent.find({},{city:1,cost:1,name:1,_id:0}).pretty()

